title: quest_start
type: panel
---
We have a quest to complete! #line:02f14b2
Guide Dante and protect him from evil! #line:0df3c65
Go speak to Dante. #line:088cd8b
//<<fight_start>>
<<target Dante>>
===
title: Dante_Intro
---
<<party_join Dante>>
When I had journeyed half of our life's way, #card:Dante #line:0a2f478
I found myself within a shadowed forest,  #line:05aa3b3
for I had lost the path that does not stray. #line:0228d43
<<target Hilltop>>
<<camera_focus Hilltop_camera>>
<<SetActive area_init false>>
<<SetActive area_hilltop true>>
===
title: Top
---
//time night
<<camera_focus Hilltop_camera>>
<<task_start reach_top>>
<<target Hilltop>>
===
title: Lynx
---
A lynx stops Dante in his tracks, forcing him to backtrack. #line:0cd2934
<<task_start Run>>
<<target Hideout>>
<<SetActive false area_hilltop>>
<<SetActive true area_lion>>

//time day
The morning sun shines on Dante, he was not out of danger yet... #line:0ba8eb0
===
title: Lion_and_Wolf
---
Quest Goal - Flee from the Lion and Wolf. #task:flee #line:001f30f

===
title: Virgil_Introduction
---
"Have pity on me, whatever you may be, a shade, a man." #card:Dante #line:0fd5718

"Not man; I once was man. Both of my parents came from Lombardy, and both claimed Mantua as native city. I was a poet, born under false and lying gods." #card:virgilio #line:081e541

"Could you be Virgil? The-" #card:Dante #line:06637f1

"We cannot talk now, the beasts will get to us, let's get moving!" #card:virgilio #line:05e67b5
===
title: Card_DivinaCommedia
---
The structure of the commedia revolves around the number 3.
3 is the number for trinity, an holy christian simbol.
<<card divina_commedia>>
===
title: Card_inferno
---
The structure of Dante's Inferno.
Dante starts from the Dark Forest to reach the Limbo.
<<card inferno>>
===
title: Card_lion
---
One of the three beasts inside the dark forest.
Lion sin of pride : one of the seven deadly sins.
<<card leone>>
===
title: Card_lynx
---
One of the three beasts inside the dark forest.
It is the symbol of lust : one of the seven deadly sins.
<<card lynx>>
===
title: Card_shewolf
---
One of the three beasts inside the dark forest.
She is the symbol of avarice : the worst sin among the 3.
<<card shewolf>>
===
title: Card_Selva
---
A dark forest where dante drifted off to.
Its an allegory for sin and cofusion.
<<card selva_oscura>>
===
title: Lynx_Start
---
A spotted lynx slips between the trees, light-footed and quick. It blocks the path and circles you.
<<fight_start>>
===
title: Lynx_Study
---
You watch the lynx's restless circling, trying to read it.
It darts in before you finish the thought.
<<fight_dodge "lynx_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    You learn its rhythm, but watching alone changes nothing. It paces, waiting.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: lynx_Provoke
---
You shout and stamp to drive the beast off.
The lynx takes it as a game and pounces harder.
<<fight_dodge "lynx_flurry">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    The provocation only sharpens its excitement. It will not be scared away.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: lynx_MatchPace
---
You slow your breathing and let your steps fall into the lynx's own restless rhythm; moving with it, not against it.
<<fight_dodge "lynx_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    The frantic circling eases. Curiosity replaces the hunger in its eyes, and it sits, tail flicking.
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: lynx_Win
---
The lynx dips its head once, then melts back into the green shadow of the wood. The path ahead is clear.
<<camera_focus Hideout_camera>>
We have to reach an Hideout with Dante, lets jump off I will protect us!
===
title: lynx_Lose
---
The lynx is too quick, too light. Your strength fails and the dark wood closes over you.
===

title: Lion_Start
---
Sun's rising and with it a new challenge approaches.
A lion strides from the thicket, head high and mane bristling. 
It will not yield the road its hunger is for your fear.
<<fight_start>>
===
title: Lion_RoarBack
---
You square your shoulders and roar back, daring it to come.
The lion answers with a charge that shakes the ground.
<<fight_dodge "lion_charge">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    Pride met with pride only makes it prouder. The lion paws the earth, ready for more.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Lion_StandTall
---
You hold your ground and refuse to look away.
The lion takes the challenge and presses you hard.
<<fight_dodge "lion_roar">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    Standing firm keeps you alive — but a locked gaze is still a challenge to a proud beast.
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Lion_ShowHumility
---
You lower your eyes, bow your head, and make yourself no threat at all.
<<fight_dodge "lion_roar">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    With no pride to push against, the lion's fury has nowhere to go. Its roar softens to a low, watchful rumble.
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Lion_Win
---
The lion regards you a long moment, then turns aside with regal grace and lets you pass.
===
title: Lion_Lose
---
The lion's pride is a mountain you cannot climb. It overwhelms you, and the road is lost.
===

title: Trio_Start
---
<<declare $lynx_calm = false>>
<<declare $lion_calm = false>>
<<declare $wolf_calm = false>>
<<set $lynx_calm = false>>
<<set $lion_calm = false>>
<<set $wolf_calm = false>>
The lynx, the lion and the she-wolf step from the wood together and ring you round. Three hungers, one road and no way back.
Get ready Dante we need to press forward! #card:virgilio
<<fight_start>>
===
title: Trio_Soothelynx
---
You turn to the restless lynx and fall into its darting rhythm, moving with it until the frenzy drains away.
<<fight_dodge "lynx_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $lynx_calm = true>>
    The lynx's circling slows; its curiosity is no longer a threat.
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Trio_SootheLion
---
You lower your eyes before the lion and offer it no pride to fight.
<<fight_dodge "lion_charge">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $lion_calm = true>>
    The lion's roar fades to a watchful rumble.
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Trio_SootheWolf
---
You meet the she-wolf's bottomless hunger with steady, unhurried resolve — wanting nothing she can take from you.
<<fight_dodge "wolf_snap">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $wolf_calm = true>>
    The she-wolf's snarl falters; for once, her hunger finds no purchase.
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Trio_AfterSoothe
---
<<if $lynx_calm and $lion_calm and $wolf_calm>>
    The three beasts circle once more, then settle as one. The road they guarded lies open.
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
<<else>>
    One beast is at peace — but the others still pace and snarl, waiting their turn.
<<endif>>
<<fight_menu>>
===
title: Trio_Win
---
The Beasts draw back together, and the dark wood parts to let you through at last.
Well done Dante, we can proceed further. #card:virgilio
===
title: Trio_Lose
---
Three hungers are too many for one road. The beasts close in, and the way is lost.
===
